### 2. Local/Remote Detection Explanation

**Local LLM Detection (Ollama):**
Startup → GET http://localhost:11434/
├─ Connection refused → Mark UNAVAILABLE (Ollama not installed/running)
├─ Timeout (>5s) → Mark UNAVAILABLE (Ollama unresponsive)
└─ HTTP 200 → Ollama is running
│
▼
GET /api/tags → Parse model list
├─ Empty list → Mark UNAVAILABLE (no models pulled)
├─ Single model → Auto-select
├─ Multiple + preferred_model matches → Use preferred
├─ Multiple + interactive_selection → CLI prompt
│ ├─ Valid input → Use selected
│ ├─ Invalid/empty → Use first model
│ └─ KeyboardInterrupt/EOFError → Use first model
└─ Multiple + no match → Use first model + log warning

text


**Remote API Detection:**
For each provider in priority order:
1. Check env var (e.g., GEMINI_API_KEY) exists
├─ Missing → Log ERROR, mark UNAVAILABLE
└─ Present → Initialize rate limiter, mark AVAILABLE

Note: We do NOT make a test API call at startup (to avoid
burning quota). Availability is based on key presence.
If the key is invalid, we discover it on first call
and mark the provider unavailable then.

